# ── ENV VARS (set these in Railway dashboard) ──────────────
SECRET_KEY=generate-a-random-string-here
UPLOAD_PASSWORD=choose-a-password-for-the-upload-page
DATA_DIR=/data

# ── DEPLOY STEPS ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# STEP 1: Push to GitHub
#   - Create a new private repo on github.com
#   - Upload all files from this folder to it
#   - (Or use GitHub Desktop if you prefer no CLI)
#
# STEP 2: Deploy on Railway
#   - Go to railway.app → New Project → Deploy from GitHub
#   - Select your repo
#   - Railway auto-detects Python and builds it
#
# STEP 3: Add a Volume (persistent storage)
#   - In Railway dashboard → your service → Storage tab
#   - Add Volume → Mount path: /data
#   - This keeps your data between deploys
#
# STEP 4: Set environment variables
#   - Railway dashboard → your service → Variables tab
#   - Add: SECRET_KEY, UPLOAD_PASSWORD, DATA_DIR=/data
#
# STEP 5: You're live!
#   - Railway gives you a URL like: sumwon-dashboard.railway.app
#   - Go to: sumwon-dashboard.railway.app/upload
#   - Upload your 4 CSV files
#   - Dashboard is live at: sumwon-dashboard.railway.app
#
# ── WEEKLY WORKFLOW ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Every Monday:
# 1. Export 4 CSVs from BigQuery (same queries as before)
# 2. Go to your-app.railway.app/upload
# 3. Enter password, drop the 4 files
# 4. Click Upload
# 5. Dashboard refreshes instantly
# 6. Send the link to the CEO
#
# ── FILE NAMES (any name works, just pick the right slot) ───
#
# Slot 1 → SHEIN Revenue    → Weekly_Trade_Table_2.csv
# Slot 2 → Inventory        → Weekly_Trade_Table_1.csv
# Slot 3 → Hit Rate Cohort  → Weekly_Trade_2-31_Cohort.csv
# Slot 4 → Webshop Data     → Webshop_per_Site_per_Week.csv
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
